This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video deblurring, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for a spatio-temporal recurrent network, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new network layer that enforces temporal consistency, which could be considered as an Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) topic. Finally, the paper involves image processing and optimization, which could be categorized under Graphics (cs.GR).
